            <p>Washington&#44; D.C. October 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1884<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>A question has been left to you to decide and I<lb/> would like to have the favor of an early reply<lb/> where was Sir Moses Montefiore born I know that<lb/> the article in Harpers last November and which<lb/> has been extensively circulated says Leghorn&#91;.&#93; I<lb/> maintain he was born in England and am <lb/> confirmed by Condensed Am Encyclopaedia Appleton<lb/> 1877. The Students Ency<hi rend="sup">a</hi> Estes and Lauriat&#91;&#63;&#93; 1883<lb/> The American Encyclopaedia Appleton 1881 vol XI p. 479<lb/> Besides this see the memorial of Sir Moses<lb/> addressed to Prince Charles of Roumania dated<lb/> August 27. 1867 &#40;to be found in the London Times<lb/> 21. Septr 1867 page 9.&#41; the following language is<lb/> used	. &#34;England my native country&#34;¬ù<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                Lewis Abraham<lb/></p>
